descript.abstract: Cell site locations within San Diego unicorporated areas. County of San Diego Department of Planning and Land Use discretionary projects layer. These data depict the location and status of Cell Sites based discretionary projects in the County of San Diego unincorporated areas. These data are only as current as the publication data and are considered void/invalid 45 days after publication date.
descript.purpose: Current planning began tracking discretionary projects in a spatial format for CEQA compliance
descript.supplinf: Points were derived from a query containing "CELL" in "PROP_CODE" and APN list of Cell towers database maintained prior to the use of the County's tracking system, KIVA. Source field in attribute table establishes were the points spatial componet is derived. either from Kiva or previous data list (PRE-KIVA)

dataqual.logic: Point represent the parcel centroid or label point for a parcel. These tupule are generate at SanGIS in the parcel landbase.

horizpa.horizpar: These points generally conform to the centroid of the assessors parcel to which they pertain. Accuracy of the point is subsequently generic and limited to indicating that the point represents a project that most likely is within the bounds of the parcel which contains it. This has numerous exceptions.

procstep.procdesc: Data extracted from KIVA through ODBC and imported into a temporary Access Database as text. These data are then imported into ArcGIS 9.+ and converted into a tupule point geodatabase.
